            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> I don't see it \"overwriting the character behind it\".\r\n\r\nI have a screencast of it here:\r\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/s/b2gbhgei5tjkskz/operator_pending_in_cmdline.mov?dl=0\r\n\r\n> What does this have to do with 'showcmd'?\r\n\r\nFrom docs:\r\n\r\n        Show (partial) command in the last line of the screen.  Set this\r\n        option off if your terminal is slow.\r\n\r\nIn normal mode, it prints \"so far typed\" characters in operator pending mode. I thought printing \"so far typed\" characters in command line is a related behavior and can be bind to same option.\r\n\r\n> Isn't the behavior the same in insert-mode?\r\n\r\nYes, it's the same in insert mode too.",
