            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "By 3 states do you mean these?\r\n1. Don't show anything.\r\n2. Show last typed character.\r\n3. Show all typed characters.\r\n\r\nThat was just a suggestion. I think it'd be nice to be able to control it, maybe with a new option. I needed this feature to update https://github.com/vim-scripts/conomode.vim so that it behaves more like normal mode in vim. I was able to do so with some tricks: https://github.com/sassanh/conomode.vim (I used `<200c>` instead of `:`)\r\n\r\nMaybe next time someone needs this feature happens 2 or 3 years later.",
